    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Conservative Is Judge Roberts?'' (editorial, Sept. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''How Conservative Is Judge Roberts?'' (editorial, Sept. 15):</p>
        <p>History teaches us that it is impossible to know the answer to that question at this time. But the public has been treated to a dazzling display of Judge John G. Roberts Jr.'s brilliance during the confirmation hearings.</p>
        <p>How can the Senate possibly reject a person of this caliber?</p>
        <p>Diana Klebanow  Forest Hills, Queens, Sept. 15, 2005</p>
        <p>The writer is an adjunct professor of political science at Long Island University.</p>
      </block>
